      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHEVAL CHIC (2) has been mixing her form, but this is a clear drop in grade from her last run at Eagle Farm over 1200m just over 3 weeks ago, and, on her best efforts, she is more than good enough to take this out. TORONESS (6) resumed with a strong win by a short-head 2 starts ago at Toowoomba and, although only fifth there last time, she was well supported and was not far off the winner. Stick with her. STREAK OF WINNING (1) found the company too strong over 1400m at Eagle Farm 15 days ago, and racing keenly during the running that day did not help him at all, but this is a far more suitable assignment, and a form reversal is expected. NIGHTCAPPED (4) had no luck off a wide run when finishing ninth over 1400m at the Gold Coast 15 days ago. She has a far better record on this circuit, and she has sound each-way claims, especially if it is wet.",
